## Question

Given an integer array `nums` and an integer `target`, return indices of two numbers such that:


nums[i] + nums[j] = target
```


# Approach

* Use `HashMap` to store:

```text id="wl7l77"
number -> index
```

* Traverse the array.
* For every element:

  * Find required value using:

```java id="8rpnjl"
target - nums[i]
```

* Check if required value already exists in map.
* If yes, return indices.
* Otherwise store current element in map.

---

# Code

```java id="6npkh6"
import java.util.HashMap;

class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {

        HashMap<Integer,Integer> hm = new HashMap<>();

        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int complement = target - nums[i];

            if(hm.containsKey(complement)) {
                return new int[]{hm.get(complement), i};
            }

            hm.put(nums[i], i);
        }

        return new int[]{};
    }
}
```
